[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6525,
        "end_time": 9349,
        "text": "Think about all the things that need to happen"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9349,
        "end_time": 11776,
        "text": "for a human settlement to thrive:"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11776,
        "end_time": 13174,
        "text": "obtaining food,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 13174,
        "end_time": 14344,
        "text": "building shelter,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 14344,
        "end_time": 16676,
        "text": "raising children and more."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 16676,
        "end_time": 18815,
        "text": "There needs to be a way to divide resources,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 18815,
        "end_time": 20542,
        "text": "organize major efforts"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 20542,
        "end_time": 23111,
        "text": "and distribute labor efficiently."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 23111,
        "end_time": 26240,
        "text": "Now imagine having to do this without any sort of planning"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 26240,
        "end_time": 28455,
        "text": "or higher level communication."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 28455,
        "end_time": 30267,
        "text": "Welcome to the ant colony."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 30267,
        "end_time": 33564,
        "text": "Ants have some of the most complex social organization"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 33564,
        "end_time": 35319,
        "text": "in the animal kingdom,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 35319,
        "end_time": 36639,
        "text": "living in structured colonies"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 36639,
        "end_time": 38697,
        "text": "containing different types of members"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 38697,
        "end_time": 40934,
        "text": "who perform specific roles."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 40934,
        "end_time": 44126,
        "text": "But although this may sound similar to some human societies,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 44126,
        "end_time": 47966,
        "text": "this organization doesn&#39;t arise from any higher level decisions,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 47966,
        "end_time": 51712,
        "text": "but is part of a biologically programmed cycle."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 51712,
        "end_time": 53305,
        "text": "In many species,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 53305,
        "end_time": 56215,
        "text": "all the winged males and winged virgin queens"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 56215,
        "end_time": 58950,
        "text": "from all the nearby colonies in the population"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 58950,
        "end_time": 61253,
        "text": "each leave from their different nests"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 61253,
        "end_time": 63932,
        "text": "and meet at a central place to mate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 63932,
        "end_time": 67655,
        "text": "using pheromones to guide each other to a breeding ground."
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 67655,
        "end_time": 70177,
        "text": "After mating, the males die off,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 70177,
        "end_time": 73236,
        "text": "while females try to establish a new colony."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 73236,
        "end_time": 76349,
        "text": "The few that are successful settle down in a suitable spot,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 76349,
        "end_time": 77739,
        "text": "lose their wings,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 77739,
        "end_time": 79659,
        "text": "and begin laying eggs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 79659,
        "end_time": 85251,
        "text": "selectively fertilizing some using stored sperm they&#39;ve saved up from mating."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 85253,
        "end_time": 87980,
        "text": "Fertilized eggs grow into female workers"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 87980,
        "end_time": 90455,
        "text": "who care for the queen and her eggs."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 90455,
        "end_time": 91951,
        "text": "They will then defend the colony"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 91951,
        "end_time": 93652,
        "text": "and forage for food,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 93652,
        "end_time": 96524,
        "text": "while unfertilized eggs grow into males"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 96524,
        "end_time": 100055,
        "text": "whose only job is to wait until they are ready to leave the nest"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 100055,
        "end_time": 102852,
        "text": "and reproduce, beginning the cycle again."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 102852,
        "end_time": 106241,
        "text": "So how do worker ants decide what to do and when?"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 106241,
        "end_time": 108054,
        "text": "Well, they don&#39;t really."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 108054,
        "end_time": 110813,
        "text": "Although they have no methods of intentional communication,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 110813,
        "end_time": 113600,
        "text": "individual ants do interact with one another"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 113600,
        "end_time": 116850,
        "text": "through touch, sound and chemical signals."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 116850,
        "end_time": 119241,
        "text": "These stimuli accomplish many things"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 119241,
        "end_time": 122674,
        "text": "from serving as an alarm to other ants if one is killed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 122674,
        "end_time": 126778,
        "text": "to signaling when a queen is nearing the end of her reproductive life."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 126778,
        "end_time": 130673,
        "text": "But one of the most impressive collective capabilities of an ant colony"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 130673,
        "end_time": 134231,
        "text": "is to thoroughly and efficiently explore large areas"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 134231,
        "end_time": 136917,
        "text": "without any predetermined plan."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 136917,
        "end_time": 139815,
        "text": "Most species of ants have little or no sense of sight"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 139815,
        "end_time": 142613,
        "text": "and can only smell things in their vicinity."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 142613,
        "end_time": 144852,
        "text": "Combined with their lack of high level coordination,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 144852,
        "end_time": 148024,
        "text": "this would seem to make them terrible explorers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 148024,
        "end_time": 149927,
        "text": "but there is an amazingly simple way"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 149927,
        "end_time": 152680,
        "text": "that ants maximize their searching efficiency;"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 152680,
        "end_time": 154358,
        "text": "by changing their movement patterns"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 154358,
        "end_time": 157099,
        "text": "based on individual interactions."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 157099,
        "end_time": 158567,
        "text": "When two ants meet,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 158567,
        "end_time": 160913,
        "text": "they sense each other by touching antennae."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 160913,
        "end_time": 164652,
        "text": "If there are many ants in a small area this will happen more often"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 164652,
        "end_time": 166698,
        "text": "causing them to respond by moving"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 166698,
        "end_time": 171761,
        "text": "in more convoluted, random paths in order to search more thoroughly."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 171761,
        "end_time": 175757,
        "text": "But in a larger area, with less ants, where such meetings happen less often,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 175757,
        "end_time": 179007,
        "text": "they can walk in straight lines to cover more ground."
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 179007,
        "end_time": 181330,
        "text": "While exploring their environment in this way,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 181330,
        "end_time": 183879,
        "text": "an ant may come across any number of things,"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 183879,
        "end_time": 186835,
        "text": "from threats or enemies, to alternate nesting sites."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 186835,
        "end_time": 191707,
        "text": "And some species have another capability known as recruitment."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 191707,
        "end_time": 194216,
        "text": "When one of these ants happens to find food,"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 194216,
        "end_time": 198266,
        "text": "it will return with it, marking its path with a chemical scent."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 198266,
        "end_time": 200863,
        "text": "Other ants will then follow this pheromone trail,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 200863,
        "end_time": 204516,
        "text": "renewing it each time they manage to find food and return."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 204516,
        "end_time": 206998,
        "text": "Once the food in that spot is depleted,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 206998,
        "end_time": 209382,
        "text": "the ants stop marking their return."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 209382,
        "end_time": 213875,
        "text": "The scent dissipates and ants are no longer attracted to that path."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 213875,
        "end_time": 216772,
        "text": "These seemingly crude methods of search and retrieval"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 216772,
        "end_time": 220654,
        "text": "are, in fact, so useful that they are applied in computer models"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 220654,
        "end_time": 224813,
        "text": "to obtain optimal solutions from decentralized elements,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 224813,
        "end_time": 228079,
        "text": "working randomly and exchanging simple information."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 228079,
        "end_time": 231134,
        "text": "This has many theoretical and practical applications,"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 231134,
        "end_time": 233967,
        "text": "from solving the famous traveling salesman problem,"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 233967,
        "end_time": 238177,
        "text": "to scheduling computing tasks and optimizing Internet searches,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 238177,
        "end_time": 241072,
        "text": "to enabling groups of robots to search a minefield"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 241072,
        "end_time": 244807,
        "text": "or a burning building collectively, without any central control."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 244807,
        "end_time": 249160,
        "text": "But you can observe these fascinatingly simple, yet effective, processes directly"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 249160,
        "end_time": 250994,
        "text": "through some simple experiments,"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 250994,
        "end_time": 254717,
        "text": "by allowing ants to enter empty spaces of various sizes"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 254717,
        "end_time": 257135,
        "text": "and paying attention to their behavior."
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 257135,
        "end_time": 261026,
        "text": "Ants may not be able to vote, hold meetings or even make any plans,"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 261026,
        "end_time": 263830,
        "text": "but we humans may still be able to learn something"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 263830,
        "end_time": 265938,
        "text": "from the way that such simple creatures"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 265938,
        "end_time": 270468,
        "text": "are able to function so effectively in such complex ways."
    }
]